cs.CV, cs.MM, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE 

This paper is about crowd counting in videos, which is a computer vision task. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a novel framework based on dynamic temporal modeling, which involves modeling the relationship between video frames, and this could fall under the category of multimedia (cs.MM). The paper also mentions the use of residual blocks and convolutions, which are common techniques in machine learning, and could place the paper under the categories of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE).
